<div class="content">
  <h1>Casper – The Soft Ghost</h1>
  <p>
    Casper appears only in two forms: a mysterious white blur in the
    distance, or a 4-kilo cloud of fur suddenly materializing on your chest
    when you try to sleep.
  </p>
  <p>
    He doesn’t meow like a normal cat. Casper’s communication style is
    mostly silent stares, slow blinks, and the occasional tiny “mrp” that
    sounds like a ghost testing a microphone.
  </p>
  <h2>Casper’s Hauntings</h2>
  <p>
    - Materializes when cans open, vanishes when the vacuum starts.<br>
    - Leaves perfectly arranged fur on black clothes only.<br>
    - Teleports between windowsills to monitor birds, neighbors, and
      imaginary threats.
  </p>
</div>

